updateEmployee(Employee, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, Long, Long) - Method in class edu.sjsu.cmpe275.api.service.implementation.EmployeeManagementService
updates the given Employee object, returns true if update is successful.
Transactional method Changing an employee’s employer through the employerId follows following steps.

If this person currently has a manager foo, all his/her current reports will report to foo.
If this person currently does not have a manager, all his/er reports will changed to not have a manager.
This person’s new manager (changed through the managerId parameter) must belong to the new company as well, or does not have a new manager.

updateEmployer(Long, String, String, String, String, String, String, String) - Method in class edu.sjsu.cmpe275.api.controller.implementation.EmployerAPIController
This method will edit an employer corresponding to the ID provided.

returns 404 if an employer corresponding to the ID is not found.
returns 400 if name provided is not unique or belongs to another employer.
returns 400 if the name is not provided in the query.
